    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I suspect the utility does it right, and OpenRA itself displays the units incorrectly.\n\nfrom http://cnc.wikia.com/wiki/Tiberian_Dawn_Mission_Manual\n\n> direction which it is facing. 0=north, 32=north-east, 64=east,\n> 96=south-east, 128=south, 160=south-west 192=west, 224=north-west.\n\nI converted a TD mission (scg30ea), when run in C&C95 1.06, the gunship faces left; after importing it into OpenRA it faces right (yaml contains \"Facing: 192\" for the boat). (After manually changing it to 64 it faces left)\n\nedit: unless there is a good reason OpenRA assigns these values counter-clockwise instead of clockwise - thinking of it, both options seem arbitrary\n"
